---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { graphSchema, webPageSchema, breadcrumbListSchema } from "../lib/schema";

const title = "Our Estimation Methodology & Material Standards";
const description = "Learn about the mathematical formulas, building code compliance checks, and engineering material density references used across HomePlanningHub.";
const canonical = "https://homeplanninghub.com/methodology/";

const schema = graphSchema(
  webPageSchema({ url: canonical, topicName: "Estimation Methodology" }),
  breadcrumbListSchema([
    { name: "Home", path: "/" },
    { name: "Methodology", path: "/methodology/" },
  ]),
);
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} schema={schema}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 py-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--fg)] transition-colors">Home</a>
      <svg class="w-3 h-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
      <span class="text-[var(--fg-secondary)] font-medium">Methodology</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="pb-6 mb-2 border-b border-[var(--border)]">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Our Estimation Methodology
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-pretty">
        Transparency is the foundation of HomePlanningHub. All calculators on our platform list their exact geometric formulas, underlying material density constants, and construction assumptions.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none text-[var(--fg-secondary)] flex flex-col gap-6">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
          1. Geometric Calculation Accuracy
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Our calculator engine performs volume and surface area math using precise standard geometry. Irregular shapes (such as L-shaped rooms or multi-sloped roof decks) are broken down into rectangular and triangular segments to prevent estimation inaccuracies.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <li><strong>Area (Rectangle)</strong>: Width × Length</li>
          <li><strong>Area (Circle)</strong>: &pi; × Radius&sup2;</li>
          <li><strong>Volume (Cylinder/Tube)</strong>: &pi; × Radius&sup2; × Depth</li>
          <li><strong>Volume (Cubic Yards)</strong>: Cubic Feet &divide; 27</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
          2. Building Code &amp; Safety Compliance
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Where appropriate, our calculators compare user inputs against standard residential building safety rules (such as the International Residential Code or IRC):
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <li><strong>Staircase Safety Alerts</strong>: Flagging steps where the riser height exceeds 9.5 inches or the walk-line tread depth is narrower than 7.5 inches.</li>
          <li><strong>Slab Thickness Recommendations</strong>: Recommending 4-inch slabs for patios and walkways, and 6-inch reinforced slabs for heavy vehicle traffic or RV pads.</li>
          <li><strong>Ventilation Rules</strong>: Applying the 1/150 rule for attics (1 sq ft of net free ventilation area per 150 sq ft of attic space).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
          3. Engineering Material Constants
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Material weight estimates use verified standard density values from engineering references:
        </p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto my-4">
          <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse text-xs">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border)]">
                <th class="py-2 font-semibold text-[var(--fg)]">Material</th>
                <th class="py-2 font-semibold text-[var(--fg)]">Standard Weight/Density</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-muted)]">
                <td class="py-2">Poured Concrete</td>
                <td class="py-2">~150 lbs / cubic foot</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-muted)]">
                <td class="py-2">Crushed Gravel / Soil</td>
                <td class="py-2">~2,800 to 3,000 lbs / cubic yard</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-muted)]">
                <td class="py-2">Carbon Steel</td>
                <td class="py-2">0.2836 lbs / cubic inch</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-[var(--border-muted)]">
                <td class="py-2">Aluminum 6061</td>
                <td class="py-2">0.0975 lbs / cubic inch</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-[var(--border)] pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
          4. Regional Labor Adjustments
        </h2>
        <p class="leading-relaxed">
          Our cost estimator modules apply regional labor cost multipliers ranging from 0.8x to 1.3x based on local economic conditions (e.g. low-cost rural vs. high-cost west coast metropolitan areas) to help homeowners align their budgets with real-world local contractor bids.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-[var(--bg-subtle)] p-5 mt-4">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold mb-1">Limitations and disclaimer</h3>
        <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed">
          Our calculators are intended solely for educational planning. Material outputs include mathematical rounding and standard waste buffers, but actual job site requirements vary based on contractor experience, exact product yields, and structural complexities. Always verify calculations with your engineer or builder before making purchases.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
